<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870304-0010 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Premier IndustrialAssigns New PostsTo Four Executives</HL><DD> 03/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PRE WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Premier Industrial Corp. said it named four top executives in a move to strengthen its senior management team &quot;to support the larger organization we are becoming.&quot;    Robert Warren, formerly president, was named to the new post of vice chairman of this maker of electronic parts for industrial, commercial and institutional applications and fire-fighting accessories. William H. Hamilton, 62 years old, formerly senior vice president, was named president, succeeding Mr. Warren, 64, who remains chief operating officer.    In addition, Premier named Philip S. Sims and Bruce W. Johnson to the new posts of executive vice presidents. Mr. Sims, 59, formerly senior vice president, will remain treasurer and chief financial officer. Mr. Johnson, 46, remains head of the company's electronics group.    Morton L. Mandel, 65, continues as chairman and chief executive officer of Premier, which had 1986 sales of $435 million. </TEXT></DOC>